1NT pass 2H pass 2S pass 3C pass 3NT pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: E, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 0, nRot: 1, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "dc20c13937c2ebe6123b32e92c50a3bc42e6f9b80a21aabb1e127282fe4035eb"]
[Category "Bidding Conventions"]
[Difficulty "beginner"]
[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/jacoby_transfers"]
[Student "S"]
{East opens 1NT.  

Initiate the transfer by bidding 2\H. After partner responds 2\S  

Your bid of a minor suit here shows at least 4 cards and is a slam try. With a weaker hand you would probably just bid 2NT or 3NT.

Having made the try, you accept whatever partner decides. In this case, with a 15 point minimum, a doubleton \S and no \C fit, partner settles on 3NT.}

